uice","2 garlic cloves","100 g brown onions, cut into halves","75 g red capsicum, cut into pieces","1 - 2 fresh jalapeño chillies, deseeded if preferred","500 g ripe mango, flesh only, cut into small pieces (1-2 cm)","2 tsp salt","100 g sugar","250 g water"]}],"id":"r156326","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-LGMBfPr7sxg\/XZQwDPknGRI\/AAAAAAAAciQ\/1gdLFQT-TsEE7YqBUeKVk0ygLPActgrVACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RVwxX-4IzW6I5FJ0.png","title":"Honey lime chicken supremes with Mango chutney","publishedAt":"2017-05-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"43 g","fat":"1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"31 g","calories":"1346 kJ \/ 321 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, large bowl, small bowl, serving dish, sealable storage jar, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["A chicken supreme is a half breast of chicken with the upper part of the wing still attached.<br>- For a stronger flavour, marinate the chicken in <b>step 2<b> for a few hours or overnight.<br>- Once it has cooled completely, the mango chutney can be stored in the refrigerator for up to two weeks or stored in freezable containers in the freezer for up to <b>6 months.<b>","For a complete meal, in <b>step 5<b> weigh 400-600g vegetables (eg carrots, potatoes, green beans, zucchinis,broccoli), cut into bite-size pieces into Varoma dish and steam until tender."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 15m","4 portions"]}